# Constant Fold COALESCE and Conditional Functions

## Description

Simplifies COALESCE, NULLIF, and CASE expressions when arguments are
constant. COALESCE(NULL, NULL, 5) becomes 5. NULLIF(1, 2) becomes 1.
CASE WHEN TRUE THEN x ELSE y END becomes x.

**When to apply**: COALESCE/NULLIF with all-constant arguments, or
CASE with constant conditions.

**Why it works**: These conditional expressions follow deterministic
rules with constant inputs. Folding eliminates branching per row.

## Implementation

```rust
rw!("fold-coalesce-first-non-null";
    "(coalesce ?a ?rest)" => "?a"
    if is_non_null_const("?a")
),
rw!("fold-coalesce-skip-null";
    "(coalesce null ?rest)" => "(coalesce ?rest)"
),
rw!("fold-nullif-equal";
    "(nullif ?a ?a)" => "null"
    if is_const("?a")
),
rw!("fold-nullif-unequal";
    "(nullif ?a ?b)" => "?a"
    if both_const("?a", "?b") && values_differ("?a", "?b")
),
rw!("fold-case-true";
    "(case (when true ?then) ?rest)" => "?then"
),
rw!("fold-case-false";
    "(case (when false ?then) ?rest)" => "(case ?rest)"
),
```

## Test Cases

```sql
-- Before
SELECT COALESCE(NULL, NULL, 'default') FROM t;
-- After
SELECT 'default' FROM t;
```

```sql
-- Before
SELECT NULLIF(1, 2) FROM t;
-- After
SELECT 1 FROM t;
```

